{"by":"metafeather","id":47762713,"parent":47757495,"text":"I&#x27;ve been using `git town`[1] for years to managed stacked PR&#x27;s alone with Github PR&#x27;s[2] and juniors I have introduced it to have really found it a helpful mental model when developing features.<p>I hope the Gitub CLI will include syncing[3] &#x27;stacks&#x27; locally with upstream in a similar way.<p>[1]: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.git-town.com&#x2F;stacked-changes.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.git-town.com&#x2F;stacked-changes.html</a><p>[2]: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;marketplace&#x2F;actions&#x2F;git-town-github-action\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;marketplace&#x2F;actions&#x2F;git-town-github-actio...</a><p>[3]: <a href=\"https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.git-town.com&#x2F;commands&#x2F;sync.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.git-town.com&#x2F;commands&#x2F;sync.html</a>","time":1776153950,"type":"comment"}